<span style="font-family: 'Playfair Display';"><span style="color: #6a99e6;"><strong>Summary</strong></span>
<span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman';"><em>Jérusalem</em> continues the action of the First Crusade itself. It describes both the foundation of the Latin Kingdom of Jerusalem with the election of Godfrey of Bouillon as King and recounts the early struggle to defend the newly conquered territory.

<span style="font-family: 'Playfair Display';"><span style="color: #6a99e6;"><strong>Representative MSS</strong>
</span><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman';">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale, MS fr.12558 (vellum, xiiimed)

